-- Legg Mason posts loss on charges
-- 
-- Fri Jul 25, 2008 8:11am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/25/us-leggmason-results-idUSWNAB274920080725

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - U.S. asset manager Legg Mason Inc ( LM.N ) posted a quarterly loss on Friday as it took charges related to a bail-out of money market funds exposed to risky securities. 

 Legg Mason, the second-largest publicly traded U.S. asset manager, reported a net loss of $31.3 million, or 22 cents a share, for its fiscal first quarter, compared with net income of $191 million, or $1.32 a share, a year earlier. (Reporting by Muralikumar Anantharaman; editing by John Wallace)